post_text:
Good evening CPA families!

Our school board just completed their virtual special meeting to discuss a change to the start date for the 2020-2021 school year. At the recommendation of the administrative team at CPA, the Board unanimously voted to approve the move of the start of school to Monday August 24, 2020.

This move allows the team additional time to complete working on technology needs identified through the completed surveys. Expect an email communication regarding this in the near future; if you indicated a need for a device.

We are so excited to hold our "Virtual Meet The Teacher" event tomorrow night. Please check your emails for a link to join your child's class. All invites will be sent by noon tomorrow.

We appreciate all of your support during this time and are excited to start our school year on August 24!

post_text:
Good morning CPA! Happy 1st day of school.

We want you to know that we are aware that school loaned iPads are having difficulty logging onto Google Meet. We are working with our technology company to figure out a fix for this. In the meantime, you can join google meetings with a smart phone if you have one. If you don't have a smart phone, you can watch the recorded meetings in google classroom. They will be posted after each meeting occurs. Please simply communicate with your child's homeroom teacher to let them know that you are having trouble getting logged on so that attendance counts for them today.

We will update you as soon as there is a solution to this problem. Thank you for your patience and understanding as we work to resolve this issue.

Update for 5th and 6th grade families only:

Hello 5th and 6th grade parents and welcome back. To have a simple mass communication tool, we are using a free app called Dojo that will link your email to ours and will allow easy exchanges of personal messages and large announcements. Below will be two different links depending on if you have a child enrolled in 5th and/or 6th grade this year. On the Dojo page already will be important information regarding pick up of school supplies that we have purchased for you already with leftover instruction funds from last year. We highly recommend that if you have a smartphone that you download the Dojo app and allow push notifications so that we can easily keep you in the loop. No worries we don‚Äôt intend on spamming your inbox!

post_text:
Happy Friday CPA families!

Updated on our school website you will find both remote daily schedules and supply lists for our students under the "Remote Learning" category. Please use these resources to help plan for the upcoming start of school year. Students not available to attend the live sessions will have recordings available in Google classroom.

https://columbuspreparatoryacademy.org/

We understand that one of the biggest questions from families is access to technology. We want to thank all of our families who completed the technology survey. We are compiling that information and working to understand our ability to help those families with technology needs. Continue to look for updates on this as it is a fluid situation and we are working with an industry high demand for devices. Expect more frequent updates in the days leading up to the start of school in regards to technology.

We look forward to the start of another great school year. Stay safe CPA families!

Happy Friday CPA family,
Please find below the first round of information pertaining to our remote learning restart for the 2020-2021 school year. We are hoping this will begin to answer some of your questions regarding the upcoming school year. Please note, we understand this is not an all inclusive list of questions and answers but we want to continue to update families as we have some of the answers. We will continue to provide Friday updates so everyone has the most up to date information. These updates will also be sent via email.
It is imperative that we have current contact information for all students. If your contact information has changed please contact the school to have it updated as soon as possible.
We are working diligently to solidify plans and are excited to share those plans with all of you. Continue to stay safe!

‚ú®üëΩ OUTTA THIS WORLD ART SHOW üöÄ‚ú®
4th grade ceramic lesson! Since we don‚Äôt have a kiln, 4th grade used model magic clay to learn ceramic techniques to create their own rocket ship or UFO relief sculptures! We began the lesson by learning ceramic vocabulary and learned basic techniques to help the students build their relief sculptures. Students sketched out their ideas, then built their design. After they were finished we completed the project by painting them with @blickartmaterials neon tempera paint!! In the art show these were supposed to be in our ‚ÄúGLOW GALLERY‚Äù, which was going to be a room full of black lights!! ‚ú®
Unfortunately, not all students were able to finishing painting before we left school. I‚Äôm still so proud of their hard work!!

Our last week of senior spotlights begins with Hunter:

"In the Fall of 2020, I will be attending The Ohio State University and I intend to major in Mathematics.

I would like all the students to remember to not take their time in high school for granted. The four years that you will spend in high school will go by faster than you think. Make sure you cherish the friends and memories that you make in high school.

I will also miss the close relationship that I had with many of the staff and teachers at CPA."

post_text:
Continuing with our Class of 2020 celebration, our senior spotlight today is Anthony!

"I plan on moving to Angola, Indiana and attending Trine University to get my Bachelors degree and eventually move towards my Masters in biomedical engineering.

My advice for all students at CPA High future and present is to take advantage of the college credit plus program because it really does make a difference in your future. Also, make sure to really really try every year because if you don't take you first two years of high school seriously it will be hard for you to make up for that time.

I will miss the community at CPA as I have always been at CPA and it's become like a second home for me."

We are so proud to have you as a member of our community, Anthony! Congratulations!

Today's senior spotlight is Malinda!

"I have decided to continue with my college education and apply for internships/work-study programs. I have been accepted into the pre-social work major at The Ohio State University. Upon which, I intend to earn a Bachelor‚Äôs degree through an accelerated three-year program the and pursue my Master‚Äôs degree under the State of Ohio‚Äôs Child and Family Services Department.

One of the most important factors in academic success is mental health. It is all too easy to become overwhelmed with taking high school classes and earning credits through the College Credit Plus program. Remember to take routine study breaks, stick to a sleep schedule, and reach out to trusted family members, friends, and adults. I will miss the small student body size at CPA. At our school, teachers and other administrative faculty can more easily align their learning material to the students‚Äô individualized learning preferences."

Congratulations Malinda! We know you will do great things!!

post_text:
Our next spotlighted senior is Aya.

"I plan on attending The Ohio State University. I'm majoring in biological sciences and plan on pursuing a Bachelor's degree.

It's important to have a balance between being a student and living your life. Work hard and put your best effort into your schoolwork, but don't let that stop you from enjoying high school. Be present and live in the moment. Four years really does fly by fast; before you know it, high school will be over and there are no do-overs. Have no regrets, and enjoy some of the best years of your life.

I will miss the CPA family the most. Everyone at CPA is there for each other no matter what and the teachers/staff always make sure everyone is taken care of. CPA has always been like home and will forever hold a special place in my heart."

Congratulations Aya! CPA is so proud of you!

Today, Ohio Governor, Mike DeWine announced that Ohio schools will remain closed to students for the remainder of this academic school year. While our hearts are feeling broken about not seeing our students again this year, we understand the importance of social distancing. We will continue to educate CPA students using our distance learning plan through the end of the school year.

Our School Board and administrative team continue to follow directives as they are laid out by the Governor, state health professionals and local government leaders. In the meantime, please reach out to us if you are in need of support. We remain committed to doing all we can as a community to support the social, emotional and educational outputs of every CPA student.

Our School Board and administrative team continue to follow directives as they are laid out by the Governor, state health professionals and local government leaders. We are strengthened in our knowledge that our CPA family is resilient and connected. We are proud to have parents and families prepared to offer help in any way they can.

Please know that as we receive updates from the Ohio Department of Education, CPA's teachers and administrative team are prepared to use all available resources to meet and exceed all ODE expectations. We remain committed to doing all we can as a community to support the social, emotional and educational outputs of every CPA student.

As some of you may know, this year's yearbook is being put together by our own students with the help of Miss Freking and Mr. Mossbarger. Our school year has taken an unexpected turn with COVID 19. It will forever be part of what makes this year a distinctively memorable one. Miss Freking and her team of students would like to include a page in the yearbook that highlights what families have been doing to stay safe, happy and healthy during stay home orders. This could mean pictures of your family biking, walking dogs, doing puzzles or playing games. Please send any photos of your family enjoying their unexpected time together to jennifer.freking@columbuspreparatoryacademy.org for consideration for this year's yearbook.

You can still purchase a yearbook by going to the link below.
https://inter-state.com/YearbookEntry/44315R

post_text: Teacher Highlight- Mr. Hribar's 5th grade science students took part in a shadow lab lesson that was a huge success! The students were learning about how the angle of light projected on opaque objects has an effect on their shadows. Most importantly, they were able to observe firsthand that the longest shadows were cast during sunrise and sunset (lowest angles) and the shortest shadows were during midday light. And of course, they did the whole lab in the dark!

post_text: Hello and Happy New Year CPA Families! Just 2 reminders: school does resume tomorrow! We will see everyone's smiling faces at 7:45! Also, please send in the re-enrollment forms that were sent home Wednesday before break. Seems that the online process is not up and running so please just fill out the paper form and send it back. There is a new option of "undecided" on the form if you are not sure of your plans for schooling next year yet. Also, if you already turned in the Proof of Residency that was asked for before Thanksgiving break then you DO NOT need to send another one for the re-enrollment form. Hope everyone had a great and well rested break and we will see you all tomorrow!

post_text:
It is with a full heart that we share this post with you. We are beyond grateful that our school family came together to help us ease the burden of costly holiday meals for those in our school community. With your generosity coupled with the help of the PTO, we were able to exceed our goal of putting together 20 bags of non perishables. We have 44 bags to offer to our very own school community!

CPA families, if you find that you have fallen upon hard times, please come to school on Wednesday, November 20th from 3:30-5:30 and take a bag home with you. Our CPA family has come together to help ensure we all enjoy this holiday season. No explanations required or questions asked. Please allow our CPA family to help your family.
